fields.title: The Little Mermaid
fields.summary: Ursula, the sea witch, makes a devious deal with Princess Ariel allowing her to meet Eric, the human prince she loves. Unaware of her true intentions, Ariel lands herself in trouble.

fields.title: Poseidon
fields.summary: On New Year's Eve, a giant wave crashes into Poseidon, a luxurious cruise liner, and flips it upside down. As the ship begins to sink, the passengers struggle to find a way to survive.

fields.title: Jaws
fields.summary: A police chief, a marine scientist and a fisherman spring into action after a white shark terrorises the inhabitants of Amity, a quiet island.

fields.title: Finding Nemo
fields.summary: After his son gets abducted in the Great Barrier Reef and is despatched to Sydney, a meek clownfish embarks on a journey to bring him home.

fields.title: Deep Blue Sea
fields.summary: A group of researchers try to find a cure for Alzheimer's disease by genetically modifying shark brains. However, trouble ensues when the now-smarter sharks hunt down their creators.

fields.title: Aquaman
fields.summary: Half-human, half-Atlantean Arthur is born with the ability to communicate with marine creatures. His motive is to retrieve the legendary Trident of Atlan and protect the water world.

fields.title: Blackfish
fields.summary: The story of Tilikum, a captive killer whale that has taken the lives of several people, underscores problems within the sea-park industry, man's relationship to nature, and how little has been learned about these highly intelligent mammals.

fields.title: The Cove
fields.summary: In Taiji, Japan, local fishermen hide a gruesome secret: the capture and slaughter of dolphins. Activist Ric O'Barry, who trained dolphins for the "Flipper" TV series, joins forces with filmmaker Louis Psihoyos and the Ocean Preservation Society to expose the brutal practice, risking life and limb in the process.

fields.title: A Shark's Tale
fields.summary: Oscar, a fast-talking fish, becomes an overnight sensation when he lies about having killed a shark. However, he soon begins to suffer the consequences of his deceptive actions.

fields.title: The Meg
fields.summary: When the members of an underwater research facility are under threat owing to a 75 feet prehistoric shark, Jonas Taylor, a deep sea diver, is hired to save them.

fields.title: Lady in the Water
fields.summary: Cleveland Heep, an apartment superintendent, encounters a girl swimming in the complex's pool and learns that she is actually a magical character from a story who wants to return to her world.
